1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:02,010
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,640
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,210 --> 00:00:07,150
I know I deserved to be told off.

4
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:09,480
I know my mom is too tired to drive.

5
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:12,950
I know you didn't want Dr. Han
to nag you the whole way,

6
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:15,390
so you stubbornly insisted
on taking the bus.

7
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:19,190
You know all that, but you'd rather
give me a hard time than support me?

8
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:23,530
I'm not giving you a hard time.
Just try to see it differently.

9
00:00:24,260 --> 00:00:25,300
How so?

10
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:30,300
Soon, you won't be able to have
moments like that with Dr. Han.

11
00:00:30,670 --> 00:00:32,700
- Why?
- Because we're getting married.

12
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:36,940
I can't argue with that.

13
00:00:37,710 --> 00:00:38,740
I knew that would work.

14
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:41,410
Go on.
Hurry and make up with your grandma.

15
00:00:42,850 --> 00:00:47,590
That's why I'm bringing some beer.
Whenever Grandma gets on my case,

16
00:00:47,790 --> 00:00:49,350
she always feels bad
and waits up for me.

17
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:52,720
Wait a minute...

18
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:55,090
Who in the world is this?

19
00:00:57,730 --> 00:00:58,730
Hold on.

20
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:01,900
She has a boyfriend.

21
00:01:02,730 --> 00:01:05,800
Why would she take a photo like this
with another guy?

22
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,040
No way...

23
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:14,750
Is this the same person?

24
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:22,820
Don't tell me she's...

25
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:27,560
Grandma, I knew you'd be here.

26
00:01:30,330 --> 00:01:31,330
Ju Ah, you...

27
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:34,470
Grandma, are you still upset?

28
00:01:36,170 --> 00:01:37,170
Grandma?

29
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,500
What is this?

30
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:42,570
What are you talking about?
It's just a picture.

31
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:44,440
Are you going to lie
to your grandma?

32
00:01:45,140 --> 00:01:46,580
Grandma, it's just that...

33
00:01:47,010 --> 00:01:48,080
Gong Ju Ah.

34
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:58,760
Your mother told me
you and Jun Hyeok were on bad terms,

35
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:01,690
so the person you were talking to...
That wasn't Jun Hyeok?

36
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:04,960
Answer me.

37
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,670
Are you... What do the kids call it?
Two-timing?

38
00:02:09,070 --> 00:02:12,540
- Grandma, it's not like that.
- Then what is it?

39
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,340
You already have a boyfriend
who's met the family,

40
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:17,340
so why did you take this picture
with Dr. Yang's son...

41
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:19,940
like you're a couple? Why?

42
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:24,820
Because this man...

43
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,950
is my boyfriend.

44
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:30,760
What?

45
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:34,860
The one who opened up my world
wasn't Jun Hyeok.

46
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:37,860
It was Dr. Yang's son,
Yang Hyun Bin.

47
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:41,400
Wait, how could you...

48
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:42,930
I'm sorry.

49
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:49,370
- Wait a minute.
- I know. I know I shouldn't.

50
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:52,380
But I couldn't just turn off
my feelings.

51
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,850
Grandma, I really like him.

52
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:58,350
You know he's a good person, right?

53
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,820
So, can't you please help me?

54
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:04,360
Absolutely not.

55
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:07,060
- Grandma...
- You...

56
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:09,290
Right now, your mother is...

57
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,430
I know.

58
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:15,930
If Mom finds out,
she'll completely lose it.

59
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,670
That's why I need you to help me.

60
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:22,040
End it before your mother finds out.

61
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:25,680
Give up on him
before you get any more attached.

62
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:27,380
Got it?

63
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:29,010
Grandma.

64
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:32,050
What? Grandma!

65
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:55,610
Mother.

66
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:57,910
Why are you out of bed? Go rest.

67
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:02,210
Were you yelling at Ju Ah?

68
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:06,180
She was being so rude to you,
so I gave her a piece of my mind.

69
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:09,450
Mother, this isn't like you.

70
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:11,960
Ju Ah will catch on.

71
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,260
All right. Just go get some rest.

72
00:04:16,460 --> 00:04:19,530
Wait, why are you going
to the kitchen at this hour?

73
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:24,400
To get rid of all the salty food.

74
00:04:25,270 --> 00:04:26,270
I just...

75
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:28,040
I was just thinking...

76
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:31,840
I'm wondering if I fed you
the wrong things.

77
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,650
Mother.

78
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:36,780
I must have done something wrong
for you to end up like this...

79
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,920
No.

80
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:42,120
No, that's not true, Mother.

81
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:47,060
If you're going to be like this,
I'll regret ever telling you.

82
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:50,830
All right.

83
00:04:54,970 --> 00:04:58,070
Honestly, Mother. I can't with you.

84
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:02,110
Go on. Get some rest.

85
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,310
Eun Bin, about those clothes
we bought earlier...

86
00:05:07,580 --> 00:05:08,580
What?

87
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:11,280
Where did she go?

88
00:05:27,570 --> 00:05:29,800
It's absurd enough
that my stepmom has a daughter,

89
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:32,570
but for it to be
Min Seo of all people...

90
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:39,240
Excuse me,
have we met somewhere before?

91
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:41,980
I don't think so.

92
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,350
I knew she looked familiar.

93
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:50,050
Wait, could she have
approached me on purpose?

94
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:53,190
Do you want to join me for a drink?

95
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:56,430
I don't really know anyone
here in Korea.

96
00:05:57,130 --> 00:05:58,600
Join me. Please?

97
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:03,070
She did approach me on purpose.
I knew it.

98
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:06,040
And I had no idea.
I just let her into our house.

99
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:10,880
So, will you meet your birth mom
before you go back to the US?

100
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,710
Who knows?
I might've already met her.

101
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,550
What time works for you?

102
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:19,520
I'm free whenever.
Whatever's best for you.

103
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,520
- How about around...
- What's going on?

104
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:25,120
She said she's already met her mom.

105
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:29,030
They both know.

106
00:06:30,630 --> 00:06:33,730
What are those two plotting
to get from our family?

107
00:06:35,170 --> 00:06:37,570
My gosh, I don't know.
My head hurts. Darn it.

108
00:06:40,910 --> 00:06:43,910
Did it go well with your grandma?
Let me know.

109
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:49,280
What? Don't tell me
she really came here.

110
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,850
You know the code.
Why did you ring the...

111
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,390
Eun Bin?

112
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,660
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

113
00:07:06,730 --> 00:07:08,200
Thank you all
for your hard work today.

114
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:10,400
Of course.
But you two did most of the work.

115
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,470
I put together a rough cut
with the footage we have so far.

116
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:17,340
- It's so good. The team loves it.
- Really?

117
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:21,280
So, what I'm getting at is,
this will air sooner than expected.

118
00:07:21,350 --> 00:07:23,010
That's not a problem for us.

119
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:26,050
- For us, the sooner the better.
- That's great to hear.

120
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:29,190
We'll be on our way then.
Thank you all for your hard work.

121
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,920
- Okay.
- All right. Get home safe.

122
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:33,460
Let us know when the clip is out
and the air date is confirmed.

123
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:35,660
- We'll let you know right away.
- Go, "Human Theater!"

124
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:41,430
Hey, try not to look so miserable
when we're filming.

125
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:46,340
I'm making sure it doesn't show,
so mind your own business.

126
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:50,340
Hey, you think maybe...

127
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:52,480
Want to go there together?

128
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,350
Go where?

129
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:56,950
You see, I...

130
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,420
I'd like to go look for my father.

131
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:04,290
Why the heck would I go with you?
Forget it.

132
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,430
Fine. Suit yourself.

133
00:08:08,230 --> 00:08:09,230
I'm heading out.

134
00:08:20,340 --> 00:08:21,610
Hi, Dr. Kang.

135
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:26,980
I know you're on sabbatical,
so I feel bad asking you to cover,

136
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:28,810
but I'm so grateful.

137
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,550
Yes. It should only be
for a few months.

138
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,750
Please be discreet about this.

139
00:08:35,450 --> 00:08:38,890
Okay, come by the clinic tomorrow.
All right.

140
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:43,530
Now, what's happened
that you need to keep quiet?

141
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,830
Well...

142
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,530
- The thing is...
- Oh, honey.

143
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,200
You heard that Mom went looking
for my father, right?

144
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,040
I was going to tell you
once we knew for sure.

145
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:58,180
But she says she thinks
she was mistaken.

146
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:01,880
But something about it
still feels off to me,

147
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:04,380
so I was thinking of going there
with Dae Han.

148
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,620
- Okay.
- Yes.

149
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:09,650
Dae Han isn't home yet.

150
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:12,460
Seriously? He got off work ages ago.
What's taking him so long?

151
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:14,790
Maybe he's on a date or something.

152
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:18,400
A date? Wait,
Dae Han is seeing someone?

153
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:21,970
<i>- I love you</i>
<i>- I love you</i>

154
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:25,600
<i>- You're the only one for me</i>
<i>- You're the only one for me</i>

155
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:28,970
<i>- Though I shout your name</i>
<i>- Though I shout your name</i>

156
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:33,640
<i>Only the silent sunset</i>
<i>burns red in reply</i>

157
00:09:33,950 --> 00:09:38,550
<i>That look in your eyes</i>
<i>when we first met</i>

158
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:48,590
<i>Was it all just</i>
<i>my own misunderstanding?</i>

159
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:55,600
<i>With your bright smile</i>

160
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:06,610
- Let's play basketball next week!
- Okay.

161
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,980
I'm going to head in now.

162
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:10,750
Thanks for everything today, sir.

163
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:15,190
- What's with the "sir?"
- Then what should I call you?

164
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:22,190
- Brother.
- I'm heading in, Mr. Gong.

165
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:26,360
- All right.
- Mom, I'm going home.

166
00:10:26,430 --> 00:10:28,730
- Okay, see you at home.
- Bye, Ji Hu.

167
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,440
- Oh, man...
- Are you okay?

168
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:37,240
I'm not okay.
Gosh, I must've been really nervous.

169
00:10:37,310 --> 00:10:38,680
My legs are like jelly.

170
00:10:39,010 --> 00:10:42,480
But Ji Hu doesn't dislike me,
does he?

171
00:10:43,710 --> 00:10:46,820
If he didn't like you, he wouldn't
have come when you called.

172
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:49,550
You're right.
Ji Hu is a thoughtful kid.

173
00:10:49,990 --> 00:10:51,920
I'm sure he knew I was sincere.
Right?

174
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:53,220
Yes.

175
00:10:54,430 --> 00:10:57,430
Thank you so much
for all your effort today.

176
00:10:57,930 --> 00:10:58,930
Tamin.

177
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,470
You got it!
You're welcome, Ms. Endorphin.

178
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:07,200
I love your smile, so I wonder
how I can make you smile every day.

179
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:09,540
That's all I ever think about.
I mean it.

180
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:13,640
And since you smiled so much today,

181
00:11:14,210 --> 00:11:15,310
I'm in a great mood too.

182
00:11:15,950 --> 00:11:16,950
My Dorphini.

183
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:20,450
Do you know
what a dolphin sounds like?

184
00:11:20,450 --> 00:11:22,420
Their mouth sticks out like this,
you know?

185
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,290
Dolphin!

186
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:27,260
Dolphin!

187
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:31,960
- Go home. You must be tired.
- Who's tired?

188
00:11:32,430 --> 00:11:34,730
Who? No, who said I'm tired?

189
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:38,140
Who says I'm tired? I'm not tired.
I'm full of energy.

190
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,600
I'm totally fine!

191
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:42,810
We're in this for the long haul,
so don't overdo it.

192
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:44,180
You think so?

193
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:47,610
But I hate saying good night.

194
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:50,920
Then,

195
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:53,750
I'll...

196
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:58,160
- I'm going home!
- Race you to the door!

197
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:00,260
Hey, don't run! You'll fall!

198
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:02,290
Get home safe! Good night!

199
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,100
Dolphin!

200
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:09,470
My gosh.

201
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,240
Jin Ah.

202
00:12:12,970 --> 00:12:15,370
How's your blind date going?
Where are you now?

203
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:19,480
I had dinner alone and took a walk.
I'm on my way home now.

204
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:22,610
- By yourself?
- Yes. By myself.

205
00:12:22,850 --> 00:12:24,580
Where did Officer Jung go?
Why are you alone?

206
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,250
Didn't Officer Jung tell you
about his situation?

207
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:30,650
He did. About his father.

208
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:33,060
So?

209
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:35,060
Why are you telling me this?

210
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:38,360
What? Are you scared
that if we start dating,

211
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,330
you'll end up leaving me
like your father...

212
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:41,330
because you think you might die?

213
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,400
Frankly, dying would be a relief.

214
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:47,770
- What?
- More often than you'd think,

215
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:51,610
we get injured or become disabled.

216
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:55,710
Plenty of other jobs are like that,
not just police work.

217
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:58,980
So, do people in those professions
just not get married or date?

218
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:00,450
No, that's not it.

219
00:13:01,190 --> 00:13:03,590
This is just my own decision.

220
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:07,760
What I mean is...

221
00:13:08,130 --> 00:13:12,560
I care for you, so I don't want you
to be miserable because of me.

222
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:16,800
So, is that a confession
or a rejection?

223
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,470
It's a rejection.

224
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:30,850
Hey! What do you mean,
rejecting you?

225
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,350
It was a confession!

226
00:13:32,850 --> 00:13:33,850
You know what, though?

227
00:13:35,050 --> 00:13:36,990
I kind of get
where he's coming from.

228
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:38,920
Get what?

229
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:42,330
That time when the guy with a knife
showed up at the clinic...

230
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,430
I was afraid
Officer Jung might get hurt,

231
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:46,700
so I tried to hold him back.

232
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:48,700
Don't go. It's too dangerous.

233
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,700
Look at me.

234
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:55,270
- I'm a cop.
- Don't get hurt.

235
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,840
Please.

236
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,580
The thing is,

237
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:06,920
if I let myself like him any more,
I think I'd just be terrified.

238
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:11,220
Rather than spend my life worrying
he'll get hurt or even die,

239
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:14,430
I'm going to end it
before I get in too deep.

240
00:14:24,570 --> 00:14:28,470
Yes, Eun Bin's here with me,
so you don't need to worry.

241
00:14:28,970 --> 00:14:31,980
She probably just had a fight
with her friends or something.

242
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:36,510
I'll have her stay here tonight,
and I'll see what's wrong.

243
00:14:37,780 --> 00:14:40,120
All right. You want some tteokbokki?

244
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:41,820
A sandwich?

245
00:14:42,650 --> 00:14:45,120
Or how about a nice cold beer?

246
00:14:46,690 --> 00:14:48,060
Okay, got it.

247
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:50,760
Here you go.

248
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:53,130
How much do you trust our stepmom?

249
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:56,530
"Stepmom?" I thought you started
calling her "Mom."

250
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,340
I used to trust her 100 percent.

251
00:15:00,270 --> 00:15:02,210
So? What's the problem?

252
00:15:08,610 --> 00:15:11,320
Hey, are you not coming home
tonight?

253
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:15,950
Do I look like
a complete fool to you?

254
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:17,350
What?

255
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,820
I really liked them.

256
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:23,330
And I was so good to them.

257
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:27,130
Who are we talking about now?
Are you talking about Woo Jae?

258
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:29,270
Woo Jae?

259
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,270
Right.
She stole Woo Jae from me too.

260
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:35,840
Yes, here it is.

261
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,480
Give that back, please. It's mine.

262
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:43,880
She came here
to take everything from me.

263
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:47,220
She's here to take away
everything I have.

264
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,420
It gives me the creeps.

265
00:16:01,870 --> 00:16:03,900
What's with that "you're pathetic"
look on your face?

266
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,940
Did you really think
you wouldn't get caught?

267
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:10,910
How did you know I got caught?

268
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:14,040
- I overheard Grandma scolding you.
- What?

269
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:16,080
The rest of the family
doesn't know, right?

270
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,450
Yes, I was keeping a lookout
in case someone overheard.

271
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:22,820
Hey, Woo Jae, what am I going to do?

272
00:16:23,290 --> 00:16:26,060
My gosh, I really thought
Grandma would take my side.

273
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:29,460
Are you serious?
Why would she take your side?

274
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:32,930
Hey, Grandma was on my side
even when I quit being a doctor!

275
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:34,730
Exactly!

276
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,500
Doesn't that prove
how serious this is?

277
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:42,170
Unbelievable.

278
00:17:28,820 --> 00:17:29,990
I should probably chop this.

279
00:17:37,630 --> 00:17:39,760
Oh, where did you have to go
so early?

280
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:43,800
Hey. The morning sun was so nice,
so I took a walk around.

281
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,440
Anyway, is that Ju Ah over there?

282
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:48,340
Yes.

283
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:51,310
She said she'll drive too,
starting today.

284
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,240
As she should.

285
00:17:54,310 --> 00:17:56,950
Did you tell Jeong Han you're sick?

286
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:58,820
Not yet.

287
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,920
The timing hasn't felt right.

288
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:02,850
Why? Did something happen again?

289
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:04,690
Did they have another fight?

290
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:11,060
What is it?

291
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:12,360
Well...

292
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:17,200
Apparently, Bucket told him
you visited Seongdam.

293
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:19,840
So?

294
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:22,710
He wants to go look for them
with Dae Han.

295
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,810
What good
could possibly come from that?

296
00:18:27,310 --> 00:18:29,650
Just let them do what they want.

297
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:31,720
Good grief.

298
00:18:35,290 --> 00:18:36,290
Mother.

299
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:39,320
You know I'm more of a coward
than I let on.

300
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:41,360
I know.

301
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:45,300
But when I say I'm okay,
I really mean it.

302
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,300
I'm a doctor, after all.

303
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:49,800
Breast cancer is no big deal
these days.

304
00:18:53,740 --> 00:18:55,040
I just came from praying.

305
00:18:55,810 --> 00:18:57,210
I prayed that
it would be nothing serious.

306
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,540
You did?

307
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:02,410
I did.

308
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:05,080
I'm not going to get upset
or fall apart.

309
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:09,990
I'm going to pull myself together
and make sure this is nothing.

310
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:12,090
So you need to stay strong, too.

311
00:19:12,590 --> 00:19:14,360
I'm right here with you, okay?

312
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:18,260
Of course. I honestly don't know
what I'd do without you.

313
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:32,080
Eun Bin, I'm off. I got you this,
so eat it when you wake up.

314
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:42,450
I'm leaving my card here for you.
So buy yourself one thing you want.

315
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:44,920
Just one. Got it?

316
00:19:59,670 --> 00:20:02,470
Well, what do we have here?
Humming to yourself this morning?

317
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:05,940
Hey, I heard you have a girlfriend.
Is that true?

318
00:20:06,510 --> 00:20:07,640
It's true, isn't it, Dae Han?

319
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:10,510
Come on, that's not true.
Who told you that? Who?

320
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:14,590
Come on, Uncle. We all know.
It's totally obvious.

321
00:20:15,450 --> 00:20:18,120
Well, look at you!
It must be true then, right?

322
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:21,160
- He already came clean to me.
- What?

323
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:24,530
- When are we going to meet her?
- Well...

324
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:27,460
I'm waiting for the right time,
Seong Mi.

325
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:30,570
Mom, when I bring my girlfriend
home,

326
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:33,840
will you make a feast
just like you did for Jun Hyeok?

327
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,040
Bring her over
when you two are serious.

328
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:39,080
Of course!

329
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:42,210
That's wonderful news.

330
00:20:42,650 --> 00:20:44,720
Congratulations, Dae Han.

331
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,550
This makes me so happy.

332
00:20:47,620 --> 00:20:49,690
Mom, want me to make you
even happier?

333
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:54,460
- Ta-da!
- What?

334
00:20:55,090 --> 00:20:56,530
- What is it?
- What?

335
00:20:56,530 --> 00:20:59,460
- And for you too, Grandma.
- My gosh, what's this?

336
00:20:59,460 --> 00:21:02,430
- My goodness.
- What's this? Do I get one too?

337
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:04,000
I got my first paycheck.

338
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,100
They're matching bracelets
for Mom and Grandma.

339
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,670
They say the whale tail pendant
brings good luck.

340
00:21:09,170 --> 00:21:12,010
Really? I could use some good luck.

341
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:14,440
We sure could. Thank you, Woo Jae.

342
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:17,610
When I make more money,
I'll get you all much nicer things.

343
00:21:18,220 --> 00:21:21,250
Hey! I get skipping your dad
and your sister,

344
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,120
but you can't just skip over me
like that.

345
00:21:23,190 --> 00:21:24,450
After everything I did to raise you!

346
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,460
Just buy me a bottle of shampoo.

347
00:21:27,090 --> 00:21:30,560
Uncle, you worked so hard
to raise me,

348
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:33,030
and now you want to take
my hard-earned money?

349
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,570
Honestly, I didn't expect anything.
Right, Ju Ah?

350
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,100
Right.

351
00:21:46,210 --> 00:21:47,840
End it before your mother finds out.

352
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:50,680
Give up on him
before you get any more attached.

353
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:57,590
Hey, so...

354
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:02,660
Were you able to smooth things over
with your grandmother yesterday?

355
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:04,130
What?

356
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,630
- Oh, yes.
- I was going to call you yesterday,

357
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,230
but Eun Bin suddenly showed up,
so I didn't get the chance.

358
00:22:10,530 --> 00:22:12,440
Eun Bin? Why?

359
00:22:13,370 --> 00:22:14,540
I don't know.

360
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:17,870
She's usually such a chatterbox,
but she's completely clammed up.

361
00:22:18,580 --> 00:22:21,610
She's the type to overreact,
so for her to be this quiet...

362
00:22:22,210 --> 00:22:23,880
I'm worried something serious
might have happened.

363
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:25,880
It's so unlike her. I'm worried.

364
00:22:34,460 --> 00:22:35,460
Hey.

365
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:38,730
- Hey, what's going on?
- It's a code red.

366
00:22:38,830 --> 00:22:40,760
Hey, wait! I have a meeting
with the fabric supplier.

367
00:22:40,830 --> 00:22:44,400
- This is more important. Let's go.
- My gosh, what is it?

368
00:22:44,470 --> 00:22:45,470
Hey!

369
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:48,970
Gosh, you scared me!
Why are you yelling?

370
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:52,740
How can you expect me not to yell?
How could you get caught?

371
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:56,810
You got caught. But confessing?
Why would you confess?

372
00:22:57,310 --> 00:22:59,920
Come on, how long was I supposed
to keep up the lie?

373
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:03,420
Then you shouldn't have lied
in the first place!

374
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:05,190
Hey! Did you even stop to think
about me in all this?

375
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,760
What does that make me?

376
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:09,760
First, you make me your boyfriend
without my consent,

377
00:23:09,830 --> 00:23:11,360
and a fake one at that?
What is all this chaos?

378
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:14,200
Hey, is this what I get
for being your friend?

379
00:23:14,430 --> 00:23:19,100
Come on, don't be so dramatic.
My grandma's too mad at me now,

380
00:23:19,170 --> 00:23:21,170
she doesn't have the energy
to be mad at you.

381
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:25,080
Besides, you're not ever going
to run into my grandma.

382
00:23:25,310 --> 00:23:26,940
Unless it's at my wedding, I guess.

383
00:23:28,410 --> 00:23:30,710
What about Dr. Han?
What if she finds out too?

384
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:32,850
How could I ever face her again?

385
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:36,650
Don't worry about that.
My grandma will never tell my mom.

386
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:38,920
She told me to handle it
before my parents find out.

387
00:23:39,990 --> 00:23:41,290
Man.

388
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:46,060
I thought my grandma was on my side.
This is hopeless.

389
00:23:46,230 --> 00:23:48,500
I haven't even been able
to tell Director Yang.

390
00:23:49,130 --> 00:23:50,130
What do I do?

391
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,300
I don't know either.

392
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:56,440
Look, I'm trying
to come up with a plan,

393
00:23:56,870 --> 00:24:00,280
but I'm so scared of being found out
that my mind's gone blank.

394
00:24:01,710 --> 00:24:05,180
Seriously, how shocked is she?
I went to her house to greet her.

395
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:09,190
She must think
I'm a total fraud, right?

396
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:10,590
Hey!

397
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:14,190
- I bet Grandma will be at the show.
- I'm going to lose my mind!

398
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:16,260
I'm one thing, but what about you?

399
00:24:16,260 --> 00:24:18,300
My grandma gets really scary
when she's mad.

400
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:22,330
My gosh, this is all...
Whose fault do you think this is?

401
00:24:23,770 --> 00:24:25,270
Darn it!

402
00:24:43,220 --> 00:24:46,690
Wait, what's her grandma doing
around here?

403
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,730
Is she here to see Dr. Han?

404
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:52,460
Or... Oh, no.
Did she come here to chew me out?

405
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:24,630
I was going to ask Ju Ah
to set up a meeting for us,

406
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:28,900
but I remembered I had your number
from the park photo you sent me.

407
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:30,900
You could've just asked me
to come to Onjeong.

408
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:32,470
Why did you come all the way here?

409
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:36,540
I'm afraid I was a bit impatient.

410
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:41,040
I know it's rude as you're so busy.
I do apologize.

411
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,010
Not at all, ma'am.
Please speak casually.

412
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:53,960
In all my years,

413
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:57,130
I never imagined
I'd do something like this.

414
00:25:57,660 --> 00:25:59,630
Yes, please speak your mind.

415
00:26:02,570 --> 00:26:04,170
I heard from Ju Ah.

416
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:06,340
That you two are dating.

417
00:26:10,370 --> 00:26:11,370
Yes.

418
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:15,010
I know that meddling in the affairs
of two grown adults...

419
00:26:15,410 --> 00:26:17,310
is crossing a line.

420
00:26:17,750 --> 00:26:20,350
I know it's a truly shameful thing
for me to be doing.

421
00:26:22,690 --> 00:26:25,220
But before our families find out,

422
00:26:26,060 --> 00:26:28,220
I need you to break up with Ju Ah.

423
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:30,860
Of course,

424
00:26:31,530 --> 00:26:34,930
the heart doesn't always
listen to reason.

425
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:40,140
Ju Ah must know this can't work out
but can't control her heart.

426
00:26:40,740 --> 00:26:43,440
That's why she had Jun Hyeok
meet us instead of you...

427
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:47,210
and tried to get me on her side
by staging a run-in during our walk,

428
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:49,350
and we even ended up
having a meal together.

429
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:52,920
Regarding that...

430
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,890
What we did was inexcusably wrong.

431
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:58,250
But...

432
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:03,460
I cannot break up with Ju Ah.

433
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:05,660
I really can't bring myself
to give up on her.

434
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:09,800
I will do whatever it takes.
I know why you're against us.

435
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:12,770
I will do everything in my power
to help our fathers reconcile,

436
00:27:12,940 --> 00:27:17,240
and since I see Dr. Han often,
I'll take my time persuading her...

437
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:18,340
No.

438
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:23,350
That's the very reason
I came to see you.

439
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:26,020
Under no circumstances do I want...

440
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:29,650
anyone else besides me
to find out about this.

441
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:32,820
Especially not Ju Ah's mother.

442
00:27:34,420 --> 00:27:37,090
- Ma'am...
- Please. I'm asking you.

443
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:40,030
I'm begging you.

444
00:27:58,650 --> 00:28:02,320
- Yes, Vice President.
- Get to my office now. Now!

445
00:28:12,430 --> 00:28:13,860
What are you doing?
What's gotten into you?

446
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:17,830
I was just wondering
if she threw a drink in your face.

447
00:28:18,470 --> 00:28:20,840
Or maybe she yanked your hair out?

448
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,270
You think this is funny?

449
00:28:22,710 --> 00:28:24,040
It is.

450
00:28:24,910 --> 00:28:29,510
Coming all the way to your office
just to tell you to break up...

451
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:30,980
It's so dramatic.

452
00:28:31,410 --> 00:28:33,680
How on earth did you know
I met her grandmother?

453
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:37,050
Mr. Park was passing by and saw you.
Lucky him.

454
00:28:37,850 --> 00:28:40,720
Mr. Park should watch his back
now that the cat's out of the bag.

455
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:43,760
I know, right?
Why did Ms. Gong have to confess?

456
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:45,960
She probably didn't want
to lie anymore.

457
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,200
Seriously, how did she get caught
with the picture frame I gave her?

458
00:28:50,030 --> 00:28:52,470
Hey, wasn't that part of your plan?

459
00:28:52,570 --> 00:28:54,100
You wanted us to get caught
on purpose, didn't you?

460
00:28:55,170 --> 00:28:58,440
Well, I'd be lying if I said
it wasn't intentional.

461
00:28:58,710 --> 00:29:01,950
- I'm the reason things progressed.
- She told us to break up.

462
00:29:02,010 --> 00:29:04,650
What did you expect?
Her blessing right away?

463
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:09,250
Still, when I heard her say it,
my mind just went blank.

464
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:12,290
Let's just tell Dr. Han.

465
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:16,160
She told me not to tell anyone.
Especially Dr. Han.

466
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:18,830
And why do you think that is?
Because she's the final boss.

467
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:21,870
I guess you're right.

468
00:29:22,130 --> 00:29:24,830
The 30-year family feud?
That's nothing.

469
00:29:24,970 --> 00:29:27,000
The real problem is the mothers.

470
00:29:28,570 --> 00:29:30,340
I think so too.

471
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:34,210
You're Pacu Nacho,
the brand expert who moves hearts.

472
00:29:34,540 --> 00:29:38,720
You can do this.
Take on the final boss sincerely.

473
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,120
Let's go!

474
00:29:44,290 --> 00:29:46,460
I'm sorry I couldn't warn you.

475
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:49,730
What? What are you sorry for?

476
00:29:50,260 --> 00:29:52,530
What did she say?
Was she really mad?

477
00:29:53,060 --> 00:29:55,800
No, she just said
what you'd expect her to.

478
00:29:56,870 --> 00:29:58,740
She told you to break up with me,
didn't she?

479
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:00,700
Yes.

480
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:05,410
- It's not because she dislikes you.
- Of course not.

481
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:07,180
I know that much.

482
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:09,780
So confident.

483
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:12,450
Confidence is all I've got.

484
00:30:14,180 --> 00:30:16,790
I was thinking,
since it's come to this,

485
00:30:16,850 --> 00:30:18,250
should we just drop the bomb?

486
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,690
Hye Su actually said the same thing.

487
00:30:20,990 --> 00:30:24,960
But your grandmother said,
"Absolutely not."

488
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:28,900
It's not like we'll break up
even if they say, "No way."

489
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,400
That's true.

490
00:30:31,170 --> 00:30:34,270
It's not like we haven't tried
to get our families to reconcile,

491
00:30:34,340 --> 00:30:37,970
so instead of waiting nervously,
let's just blow the whole thing up.

492
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,040
And then what?

493
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:43,210
And then, we'll just...

494
00:30:43,450 --> 00:30:45,720
move in together at your place.

495
00:30:47,380 --> 00:30:50,790
I can do it.
Quitting my doctor job was hard.

496
00:30:51,020 --> 00:30:53,620
I'm a real go-getter.
I do what I say I will.

497
00:30:54,090 --> 00:30:56,390
Okay, I get it, but...

498
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,260
Let me be the one to do it.

499
00:31:00,100 --> 00:31:01,260
You're going to be
in so much trouble.

500
00:31:02,370 --> 00:31:04,630
I should be. I deserve it.

501
00:31:07,970 --> 00:31:11,740
Don't go confronting
your grandmother...

502
00:31:11,810 --> 00:31:14,540
about what she said to me.
It'll only make things worse.

503
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:15,680
Got it?

504
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:18,880
Hug me.

505
00:31:20,550 --> 00:31:23,350
- Are you crazy? We're at work.
- You've changed.

506
00:31:24,690 --> 00:31:26,060
Gosh, hey!

507
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:27,860
- Are you running away from me?
- Hey, stop!

508
00:31:33,300 --> 00:31:36,370
Jeong Sun. You are Jeong Sun, right?

509
00:31:37,070 --> 00:31:38,070
Im Jeong Sun.

510
00:31:43,310 --> 00:31:44,370
Don't be scared.

511
00:31:44,970 --> 00:31:46,240
You're Cha Se Ri now.

512
00:31:47,010 --> 00:31:48,850
No one knows the real you.

513
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:58,720
- Dong Suk. You haven't left yet?
- I was just about to. By the way,

514
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:00,520
aren't you having a grand opening
for your shop?

515
00:32:00,890 --> 00:32:03,890
It's not a restaurant,
so there's nothing to serve.

516
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:07,530
It's just a change in ownership.
Why make a big fuss over nothing?

517
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:11,530
True. Considering our grand opening,
you're better off not having one.

518
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:16,070
How are things with your boyfriend?

519
00:32:16,510 --> 00:32:19,180
- Good.
- Gosh, you're not even denying it.

520
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:22,350
My gosh, I don't know.
I'm tired of hiding it.

521
00:32:23,380 --> 00:32:26,680
I guess you're finally sure
of how you feel, right?

522
00:32:27,450 --> 00:32:31,390
He's such a great guy,
I couldn't push him away anymore.

523
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,990
That's so great.

524
00:32:34,990 --> 00:32:39,760
About my brother having
Hyun Bin and Eun Bin...

525
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:41,400
Were you really okay with that?

526
00:32:42,270 --> 00:32:46,100
I was. Why?
Does he have a problem with Ji Hu?

527
00:32:46,470 --> 00:32:50,540
- No, he's great with him.
- What a relief.

528
00:32:52,010 --> 00:32:53,680
To be honest,

529
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:56,350
I thought you were just
putting on an act.

530
00:32:56,680 --> 00:33:00,180
I wondered how anyone could raise
someone else's kids as their own.

531
00:33:01,380 --> 00:33:02,450
But...

532
00:33:03,250 --> 00:33:06,020
I see now that
good people like that do exist.

533
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:10,230
So does that make me a good person?

534
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:14,300
Of course.
You raised a handful like Eun Bin.

535
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:15,530
That's really something.

536
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:19,840
She's much better now, though.
When Eun Bin was a kid...

537
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:23,410
- I don't want to think about it.
- My gosh, tell me about it.

538
00:33:24,470 --> 00:33:27,080
But she was such a cute kid
back then.

539
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:29,750
But why did she go over
to Hyun Bin's yesterday?

540
00:33:30,310 --> 00:33:33,520
I wonder if something happened
at her part-time job.

541
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,220
I doubt it.

542
00:33:36,090 --> 00:33:37,290
Do you know something?

543
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:41,460
I don't.
I know nothing about the bookstore.

544
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:43,690
Just a guess. You should get going.

545
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:56,910
My gosh, where is Eun Bin?
We're about to open.

546
00:33:57,170 --> 00:33:58,640
Didn't you two come
from home together?

547
00:33:58,710 --> 00:34:01,010
No. She slept over at her brother's.

548
00:34:01,380 --> 00:34:03,080
I see.

549
00:34:03,810 --> 00:34:06,720
- I'm going to clean up out front.
- Okay.

550
00:34:07,180 --> 00:34:09,290
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

551
00:34:29,770 --> 00:34:30,910
(My Woo Jae)

552
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:42,190
Eun Bin, hurry over.
I've got something for you.

553
00:34:44,290 --> 00:34:45,790
I won't let you take anything
from me.

554
00:34:47,160 --> 00:34:50,460
You're not taking anything from me.
Not my mom,

555
00:34:50,990 --> 00:34:52,760
and not Woo Jae either.

556
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:15,520
We don't have many patients
this afternoon.

557
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:18,350
- So you can manage on your own.
- Yes, I know.

558
00:35:19,220 --> 00:35:21,860
When you're done filming,
go check on Se Ri.

559
00:35:22,890 --> 00:35:24,530
She must be swamped
with opening her shop.

560
00:35:24,930 --> 00:35:26,430
You can't just focus
on your own work.

561
00:35:26,930 --> 00:35:28,230
I was already planning on it.

562
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:29,770
I'll be sure
to check in on her more.

563
00:35:31,930 --> 00:35:32,940
What?

564
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:36,310
Yes, Councilor Hwang.

565
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:39,210
I'm surprised to be hearing
from you directly.

566
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,280
Pardon?

567
00:35:41,940 --> 00:35:42,980
Yes.

568
00:35:43,450 --> 00:35:45,620
If you would do that,
it would be a tremendous honor.

569
00:35:47,850 --> 00:35:50,890
Hey, the two of us will be fine.
Why would you tag along?

570
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:53,860
Because you two always fight
when you're together.

571
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:54,960
I'm going to play referee.

572
00:35:55,790 --> 00:35:56,790
Hey, Dae Han.

573
00:35:57,290 --> 00:36:01,060
If you're free this weekend,
come with me to Seongdam.

574
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:02,500
Seongdam? Why?

575
00:36:02,930 --> 00:36:05,200
To look for our father.

576
00:36:06,070 --> 00:36:07,840
What are you talking about?
Where did that come from?

577
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:11,570
Listen, someone said they saw a man
who looks just like him.

578
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:13,610
Come on, that's not the first time
we've heard that.

579
00:36:13,910 --> 00:36:16,550
Well, I know. I agree, but...

580
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:20,020
I just have a bad feeling
about it this time.

581
00:36:21,380 --> 00:36:22,390
Just us?

582
00:36:22,890 --> 00:36:23,920
He's coming too, right?

583
00:36:24,890 --> 00:36:26,820
Hey, are you guys ready?

584
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,590
Let's get going already.

585
00:36:30,290 --> 00:36:32,160
- Dae Han, are you coming too?
- Yes.

586
00:36:32,330 --> 00:36:33,860
He doesn't want to come with me.

587
00:36:35,460 --> 00:36:37,600
Goodness.
You're acting like a total kid.

588
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,200
Hey.

589
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:42,510
I just got off the phone
with Councilor Hwang.

590
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:45,980
Looks like Jeong Han really did
put in a good word for me.

591
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:50,680
See, I told you.
Do you finally believe me now?

592
00:36:51,150 --> 00:36:52,280
Sorry about that.

593
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:55,350
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings,
so just let it go.

594
00:36:55,750 --> 00:36:57,820
Don't worry.
You didn't hurt my feelings.

595
00:36:59,090 --> 00:37:01,520
Hey, what are you guys doing?
Hurry up!

596
00:37:01,990 --> 00:37:03,230
Seriously... What?

597
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:05,900
My gosh.

598
00:37:07,300 --> 00:37:08,830
Oh, yes, Director.

599
00:37:10,130 --> 00:37:11,130
Sorry?

600
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:14,300
Yes, okay. I understand.

601
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:17,670
No, it's fine.
It's nice to get a break.

602
00:37:18,170 --> 00:37:19,180
Yes, okay.

603
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:20,980
My gosh.

604
00:37:22,450 --> 00:37:24,510
What is it? What did he say?

605
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:28,850
They didn't get the film releases,
so we have to postpone.

606
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:32,090
Darn it. I canceled
all my afternoon appointments.

607
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:35,630
Hey, Gong Dae Han.
Since we're free, let's go today!

608
00:37:35,860 --> 00:37:36,860
To Seongdam.

609
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:39,600
Do you want to come with us?

610
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:43,670
- What?
- He doesn't want to. Why ask?

611
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:46,400
- Sure. Yes, let's go.
- Yes.

612
00:37:46,740 --> 00:37:50,410
Goodness, you're so fickle.
But we're taking your car.

613
00:37:50,770 --> 00:37:51,840
Of course, we are.

614
00:37:52,310 --> 00:37:55,340
- Coming from the guy with no car.
- Shut it. Come on, let's go!

615
00:37:56,410 --> 00:37:57,410
Good grief.

616
00:37:59,780 --> 00:38:00,780
You're not coming?

617
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:03,520
No, you two go. I have a date.

618
00:38:05,020 --> 00:38:06,020
Hey.

619
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:07,760
You got a girlfriend?

620
00:38:08,260 --> 00:38:09,260
Yes.

621
00:38:09,660 --> 00:38:10,760
Good for you.

622
00:38:11,660 --> 00:38:12,660
Is she pretty?

623
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:14,400
She looks like you.

624
00:38:15,870 --> 00:38:17,030
You call that pretty?

625
00:38:17,530 --> 00:38:18,530
Gorgeous.

626
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:21,240
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

627
00:38:23,770 --> 00:38:26,510
- Hey, are you coming or what?
- Yes, I'm coming.

628
00:38:40,220 --> 00:38:41,220
My gosh.

629
00:38:42,190 --> 00:38:44,430
Hey, can you watch the road?
Seriously!

630
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:46,130
Unbelievable.

631
00:38:47,330 --> 00:38:48,830
Oh, boy.

632
00:38:50,970 --> 00:38:53,670
Wow, Seongdam is a madhouse.

633
00:38:55,540 --> 00:38:56,540
My gosh.

634
00:38:56,740 --> 00:39:00,680
Man, I have no idea
where to even start looking.

635
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:02,850
I should've at least
brought a photo.

636
00:39:03,510 --> 00:39:07,620
What good is a 30-year-old picture?
Like that's going to help.

637
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:09,950
Who's the one who dragged us
out here on a whim?

638
00:39:10,090 --> 00:39:13,690
Whatever.
You go your way, and I'll go mine.

639
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:16,190
Hey, you want to split up?

640
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:18,130
You want to hold hands
and walk around together?

641
00:39:18,460 --> 00:39:22,530
- Then why did we both come?
- Hey, I don't know my way around,

642
00:39:22,830 --> 00:39:24,330
and I have no idea where to go.

643
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:27,500
You think I do? We just have to look
around everywhere, okay?

644
00:39:27,870 --> 00:39:32,510
Just look closely at every old woman
who passes by. It's not that hard.

645
00:39:33,810 --> 00:39:34,810
Darn it.

646
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:43,920
- Oh, for crying out loud.
- What?

647
00:39:45,450 --> 00:39:47,290
Hey, why are you following me?

648
00:39:47,390 --> 00:39:51,030
You check the old men passing by.
I'll check the old women.

649
00:39:51,090 --> 00:39:54,000
You're acting like a little kid.
Honestly.

650
00:39:54,060 --> 00:39:55,060
This is ridiculous.

651
00:39:56,100 --> 00:39:57,670
- Excuse me, sir?
- Yes?

652
00:39:57,670 --> 00:39:59,870
Hello, sir. Yes, I'd like to ask you
a quick question.

653
00:40:00,300 --> 00:40:04,340
Do you know where elderly folks
hang out around here?

654
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:06,010
- Hello, sir.
- Yes.

655
00:40:06,010 --> 00:40:09,080
Hey! I was in the middle of asking.
What are you doing here?

656
00:40:09,150 --> 00:40:11,280
I was busy searching too, you know.

657
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:12,380
Seriously...

658
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:13,950
- Sorry about that, sir.
- It's all right.

659
00:40:13,950 --> 00:40:15,820
- I'm sorry.
- If I could just ask you one thing.

660
00:40:15,890 --> 00:40:17,450
We're looking for an elderly man
and woman.

661
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:19,660
- There's Mr. Bong...
- Yes.

662
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:23,290
- At 101 and...
- And 177? Write it down! Hurry!

663
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:27,560
- I think it's around here, right?
- Exactly.

664
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:28,800
Man, I'm exhausted.

665
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:31,470
- Sir, can we ask you a question?
- Hello, sir.

666
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:33,270
- Sure.
- Do you know where this address is?

667
00:40:33,340 --> 00:40:36,410
- Yes.
- Head this way. It's right there.

668
00:40:36,470 --> 00:40:39,010
- Okay, thank you.
- Oh, this way? Thank you.

669
00:40:39,010 --> 00:40:40,040
Hey, it's this way.

670
00:40:43,350 --> 00:40:44,410
(Iron Pot Sundaeguk)

671
00:40:48,620 --> 00:40:49,850
Food? Now?

672
00:40:53,190 --> 00:40:54,690
- What?
- Yes.

673
00:40:55,290 --> 00:40:56,290
Fine.

674
00:40:57,690 --> 00:40:58,690
Thank you.

675
00:40:59,430 --> 00:41:01,830
Wow, this soup is incredible.

676
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,900
You think everything tastes good,
don't you?

677
00:41:04,300 --> 00:41:07,140
What are you talking about?
I have a very refined palate.

678
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:08,940
That's a laugh.

679
00:41:09,270 --> 00:41:12,370
You're the one who'd chew on rubber
if I told you it was gum. Remember?

680
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:13,440
I don't know
what you're talking about.

681
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:19,920
Hello. One sundaeguk to go, please.

682
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:25,120
Hey. Go check that lady's face.

683
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:27,260
It's probably not her, but...

684
00:41:28,290 --> 00:41:29,290
Okay.

685
00:41:30,290 --> 00:41:31,590
Ma'am?

686
00:41:32,330 --> 00:41:33,400
Hey, it's not her.

687
00:41:33,700 --> 00:41:34,760
- What?
- My goodness.

688
00:41:34,830 --> 00:41:35,830
I'm so sorry.

689
00:41:36,230 --> 00:41:37,470
Gosh, that startled me.

690
00:41:37,530 --> 00:41:41,170
My gosh, we're so sorry.
We thought you were someone else.

691
00:41:41,340 --> 00:41:42,770
- We're sorry.
- So sorry.

692
00:41:44,910 --> 00:41:45,910
Hey, once we finish eating,

693
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:49,040
- let's check the other alleys too.
- Yes, okay, sure.

694
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:52,820
- We have to check every house.
- Your takeout is ready.

695
00:41:55,550 --> 00:41:56,550
Oh, man.

696
00:41:58,020 --> 00:41:59,260
(Custom Tailoring and Alterations)

697
00:42:00,260 --> 00:42:01,260
My goodness.

698
00:42:04,130 --> 00:42:06,230
(Alterations)

699
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:12,300
Gi Cheol, the cops are here.

700
00:42:14,170 --> 00:42:17,410
Come on, hurry! The cops!
Here, be careful.

701
00:42:19,910 --> 00:42:20,910
Get inside.

702
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:28,420
(Temporarily Closed,
Closed Due to Personal Reasons)

703
00:42:32,450 --> 00:42:34,390
(CCTV in Operation)

704
00:42:34,460 --> 00:42:36,530
Hang on, I think this is the area.

705
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:39,300
- Is this the place?
- I think so. Yes.

706
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:41,660
Hey, let's just go check it out.
Go on. We'll know when we get there.

707
00:42:41,730 --> 00:42:44,930
(CCTV in Operation)

708
00:42:45,100 --> 00:42:46,200
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

709
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,070
Eun Bin, this...

710
00:42:51,740 --> 00:42:54,410
Right. Eun Bin's not here.

711
00:42:54,780 --> 00:42:57,710
(Discount on your first order
of any meat dish)

712
00:43:04,620 --> 00:43:07,390
(Hey, Eun Bin...)

713
00:43:34,020 --> 00:43:37,320
What is this? They're playing dumb.
Such great actors.

714
00:43:38,450 --> 00:43:41,020
They're living together
and hiding it from everyone.

715
00:43:41,020 --> 00:43:42,020
The nerve.

716
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:44,630
- You little brat!
- Gosh, you scared me!

717
00:43:44,960 --> 00:43:47,730
I thought you'd show Grandpa and Dad
you're working hard...

718
00:43:47,830 --> 00:43:49,300
so they'd fund your business.

719
00:43:49,900 --> 00:43:50,970
What about it?

720
00:43:50,970 --> 00:43:53,770
So is it okay to just ditch work
and fool around like this?

721
00:43:53,870 --> 00:43:57,470
- Let go! Let go of me!
- Yang Eun Bin!

722
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:04,510
Just when I thought you'd behave,
you start acting up again!

723
00:44:05,180 --> 00:44:08,020
No, Father, it's not like that.
We were just kidding around.

724
00:44:08,650 --> 00:44:10,490
You don't know anything, Grandpa!

725
00:44:11,850 --> 00:44:14,320
Just you wait.
I'll bring everything to light.

726
00:44:32,910 --> 00:44:34,740
Just drive me around
for two more weeks.

727
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:38,650
Why? What's in two weeks?
You hiring a chauffeur?

728
00:44:40,250 --> 00:44:42,580
Do you really hate driving around
with me that much?

729
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:45,250
It's because you nag me constantly.

730
00:44:45,650 --> 00:44:48,320
Once you're married, I won't get to,
even if I want to.

731
00:44:48,420 --> 00:44:50,030
And that's why I'm doing this.

732
00:44:50,890 --> 00:44:54,000
Let's try not to fight
for the little time we have left.

733
00:44:59,200 --> 00:45:01,270
Sometimes,
I'm really jealous of you.

734
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:04,810
Of what? My youth and good looks?

735
00:45:06,510 --> 00:45:09,080
That you have a mom to have these
knock-down, drag-out fights with.

736
00:45:12,650 --> 00:45:17,190
You can blame me, scream at me,
and be as bratty as you want,

737
00:45:18,250 --> 00:45:20,220
but by the next day,
it's like nothing happened.

738
00:45:20,990 --> 00:45:21,990
I'm jealous of that.

739
00:45:24,090 --> 00:45:26,860
Yes. When I have a daughter someday,

740
00:45:27,300 --> 00:45:29,400
I'll be sure to be just like you.

741
00:45:30,830 --> 00:45:34,570
Okay. And when you have a daughter
exactly like you,

742
00:45:34,570 --> 00:45:35,670
then you'll know
what I went through.

743
00:45:37,570 --> 00:45:38,740
Yes, I get it.

744
00:45:39,340 --> 00:45:40,340
Don't be late tomorrow.

745
00:45:40,610 --> 00:45:42,140
Director Yang wants
to talk to you afterwards.

746
00:45:42,780 --> 00:45:44,410
Director Yang? Why?

747
00:45:46,180 --> 00:45:47,180
You'll find out when you see him.

748
00:45:47,720 --> 00:45:49,120
You should brace yourself.

749
00:45:49,720 --> 00:45:51,290
Brace myself? For what?

750
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:53,890
There's just something.

751
00:45:59,290 --> 00:46:01,900
- Hey, you're home.
- We're home.

752
00:46:05,130 --> 00:46:07,670
Has she said anything
out of the ordinary?

753
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:09,240
Like what?

754
00:46:09,670 --> 00:46:10,970
Nothing. I was just wondering.

755
00:46:11,470 --> 00:46:13,410
- I'm going to get changed.
- Okay.

756
00:46:16,910 --> 00:46:20,180
I guess he hasn't told Ju Ah.

757
00:46:24,950 --> 00:46:27,190
I just played dumb
in front of my grandma.

758
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:28,620
Hold on.

759
00:46:31,590 --> 00:46:33,830
I really wanted to confront her
and ask how she could do that,

760
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:37,130
but I held back,
afraid she'd come to hate you.

761
00:46:37,300 --> 00:46:39,600
Good call. I appreciate it.

762
00:46:40,370 --> 00:46:43,540
And I told my mom you had something
to talk to her about tomorrow.

763
00:46:43,870 --> 00:46:47,540
I know I acted all tough
and said I'd tell her.

764
00:46:48,380 --> 00:46:49,380
I'm actually pretty nervous.

765
00:46:51,780 --> 00:46:54,250
And my mom mentioned this
on our way home.

766
00:46:54,650 --> 00:46:57,490
It looks like our fathers
patched things up a bit today.

767
00:46:58,220 --> 00:47:01,020
It's not the fathers we worry about,
it's the mothers.

768
00:47:02,460 --> 00:47:03,460
True.

769
00:47:09,230 --> 00:47:10,230
I'm back.

770
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:13,600
What's that?

771
00:47:14,140 --> 00:47:15,500
You're not good at hiding things,
are you?

772
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:17,740
Please pretend you didn't see that.

773
00:47:18,370 --> 00:47:20,110
Are you keeping another secret
from me?

774
00:47:21,510 --> 00:47:24,150
Well, actually...

775
00:47:25,310 --> 00:47:28,180
I've started studying English.

776
00:47:28,550 --> 00:47:29,550
Really?

777
00:47:30,190 --> 00:47:34,220
Running a business and studying now?
I'm so impressed with you, Se Ri.

778
00:47:35,190 --> 00:47:39,360
I just really want to be someone
who deserves to be by your side.

779
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:41,500
You already make me more than proud.

780
00:47:42,100 --> 00:47:45,330
How are you learning?
In a class? Online course?

781
00:47:45,670 --> 00:47:49,300
No. Min Seo offered to teach me
when she's not tutoring Ji Hu.

782
00:47:49,640 --> 00:47:52,210
That's great. That's nice of her.

783
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:55,940
The more I'm around that kid,
the more I like her.

784
00:47:56,450 --> 00:47:59,920
She helps me out a lot,
and she catches on so quickly.

785
00:48:00,150 --> 00:48:03,350
Yes, she's so quiet,
it's like she's barely there.

786
00:48:03,620 --> 00:48:05,750
And she never does anything
to get on your nerves. Right?

787
00:48:06,020 --> 00:48:07,190
I hope she sticks around
for a while.

788
00:48:07,990 --> 00:48:09,360
I'll talk to her.

789
00:48:09,990 --> 00:48:12,530
Any luck with your errand today?

790
00:48:13,700 --> 00:48:15,230
Of course, we didn't find them.

791
00:48:15,660 --> 00:48:17,170
Did you think
we'd find them on the first try?

792
00:48:18,100 --> 00:48:20,070
You should have started looking
sooner.

793
00:48:20,770 --> 00:48:22,470
Back then, my father didn't want to.

794
00:48:23,340 --> 00:48:26,310
He said he'd break my legs
if I went looking for my mother.

795
00:48:27,280 --> 00:48:30,410
But now that he's older,
I think he wants to find her.

796
00:48:31,750 --> 00:48:34,780
Honey, why don't you start
by filing a missing person report?

797
00:48:35,750 --> 00:48:36,790
A missing person report?

798
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:40,760
It'll be much faster
if we get the police involved.

799
00:48:41,190 --> 00:48:44,030
Let's find him now,
while your mother's still on board.

800
00:48:45,190 --> 00:48:46,830
I'll think about it.

801
00:48:47,700 --> 00:48:51,970
By the way, I have breast cancer.
It's stage two.

802
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:56,070
I had an ultrasound
at Yu Jin's clinic.

803
00:48:56,410 --> 00:48:58,870
The nodule looked bad,
so I got a biopsy.

804
00:49:00,540 --> 00:49:01,640
Size of the tumor?

805
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:03,450
Three centimeters.

806
00:49:04,180 --> 00:49:05,550
And no spread to the lymph nodes?

807
00:49:06,050 --> 00:49:09,820
The ultrasound didn't show anything,
but we can't know for sure yet.

808
00:49:10,650 --> 00:49:12,850
Yu Jin got me in
with Breast Surgery.

809
00:49:12,850 --> 00:49:14,090
I'm going in tomorrow.

810
00:49:14,890 --> 00:49:16,790
Can you step out
during your lunch break?

811
00:49:17,760 --> 00:49:19,490
Yes, sure.

812
00:49:20,300 --> 00:49:21,730
Does Mom know?

813
00:49:22,300 --> 00:49:23,770
Yes. Just Mother.

814
00:49:24,900 --> 00:49:27,040
We'll tell the kids later.

815
00:49:28,740 --> 00:49:29,840
Okay.

816
00:49:30,370 --> 00:49:31,640
I'm going to go wash up.

817
00:49:38,310 --> 00:49:41,480
His calm reaction is nice, I guess,
but I feel a bit let down.

818
00:49:44,250 --> 00:49:46,720
Still, that's just like
Gong Jeong Han.

819
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:56,470
(Myungjin University Hospital)

820
00:49:56,530 --> 00:50:01,140
The MRI shows it's a single lesion
with no additional ones,

821
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:04,440
and there's no suspicion
of lymph node involvement,

822
00:50:04,610 --> 00:50:06,910
so as long as the surgery goes well,
you should be fine.

823
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:09,640
I just have to hope
there's no micrometastasis.

824
00:50:11,150 --> 00:50:13,320
I'm worried I might need chemo.

825
00:50:13,720 --> 00:50:16,020
Don't borrow trouble.

826
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:18,990
Let's just get through the surgery
and see the pathology report first.

827
00:50:20,490 --> 00:50:21,490
Right.

828
00:50:22,190 --> 00:50:25,390
Oh, wait.
What about the clinic, the show,

829
00:50:25,460 --> 00:50:27,260
and your modeling work?
What will you do about all that?

830
00:50:27,900 --> 00:50:29,200
I'll have to take time off.

831
00:50:29,730 --> 00:50:31,970
I'll figure it out.
Don't worry about it.

832
00:50:32,200 --> 00:50:34,940
Must be nice
to finally get some time off, right?

833
00:50:35,400 --> 00:50:38,070
Yes, I bet it's just great.

834
00:50:38,670 --> 00:50:43,380
Come on, it's not a big deal, right?
Many people get cancer these days.

835
00:50:43,450 --> 00:50:46,280
And medical tech is so advanced now.
Come on.

836
00:50:47,480 --> 00:50:49,820
Right. Let's think positively.

837
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:51,920
You should get going.

838
00:50:52,220 --> 00:50:53,590
Your appointments are probably
backed up.

839
00:50:54,090 --> 00:50:57,730
Right. I'm late. I'll get going.
Okay? I'm off.

840
00:51:09,940 --> 00:51:13,110
- I'm back.
- You're back early.

841
00:51:13,310 --> 00:51:15,380
Didn't you even take her out
for a meal?

842
00:51:15,880 --> 00:51:17,610
No, we were both busy
with appointments,

843
00:51:17,910 --> 00:51:20,380
and Seong Mi said she had to
practice her walk today.

844
00:51:20,750 --> 00:51:21,750
Mom...

845
00:51:22,280 --> 00:51:24,220
You heard the results
from Seong Mi, right?

846
00:51:25,020 --> 00:51:27,490
Yes. She called me.

847
00:51:28,590 --> 00:51:30,390
Come on, don't worry too much.

848
00:51:30,690 --> 00:51:32,560
It's very common these days,
especially at her age.

849
00:51:35,300 --> 00:51:40,140
Don't walk around with a long face
like it's the end of the world.

850
00:51:40,900 --> 00:51:42,800
Is that what you said to Seong Mi?

851
00:51:43,040 --> 00:51:45,110
Pardon? Yes.

852
00:51:46,170 --> 00:51:48,910
I don't get how you're so dedicated
to your patients...

853
00:51:49,210 --> 00:51:51,780
but have absolutely no empathy
when it comes to Seong Mi.

854
00:51:51,880 --> 00:51:56,490
What are you talking about?
Because it's really not a big deal.

855
00:51:56,820 --> 00:51:58,690
I have to get to my patients. Bye.

856
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:08,200
Yes.

857
00:52:10,300 --> 00:52:12,530
- You heading out?
- Yes. You?

858
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:16,140
I'm heading to my part-time job.
Where are you off to?

859
00:52:16,710 --> 00:52:19,170
I've got to go meet someone.

860
00:52:20,340 --> 00:52:21,480
But I'm so nervous.

861
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:24,510
Who is it? Want me to come with you?

862
00:52:24,610 --> 00:52:26,550
No, it's fine.
You have to get to work.

863
00:52:26,750 --> 00:52:27,950
Especially since
you skipped yesterday.

864
00:52:28,920 --> 00:52:31,450
It's fine.
It's my aunt's restaurant anyway.

865
00:52:32,020 --> 00:52:33,590
I mean, I'd love it
if you came with me.

866
00:52:34,390 --> 00:52:36,630
- Really?
- Yes.

867
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:49,470
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

868
00:52:51,070 --> 00:52:52,940
- Good morning. Hi.
- Hello.

869
00:52:55,640 --> 00:52:56,680
Where's Eun Bin?

870
00:52:57,750 --> 00:53:00,320
This is why you don't hire
your own niece.

871
00:53:00,620 --> 00:53:02,380
That girl... I knew she'd do this.

872
00:53:03,250 --> 00:53:04,490
So she's not coming in today either?

873
00:53:05,620 --> 00:53:08,390
Right. She has something to do.
Unbelievable.

874
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:11,130
My gosh, should I just fire her?

875
00:53:19,770 --> 00:53:21,370
Why did we come here?

876
00:53:22,340 --> 00:53:25,470
I'm here to see one of the Sisters.

877
00:53:25,970 --> 00:53:27,410
A Sister? Why?

878
00:53:28,210 --> 00:53:31,810
My birth mom had me
at this home for unwed mothers.

879
00:53:32,010 --> 00:53:34,580
She raised me here until I was one,
then put me up for adoption.

880
00:53:36,250 --> 00:53:40,260
So you were adopted and went
to the US when you were one?

881
00:53:40,890 --> 00:53:43,120
No, I was adopted here in Korea.

882
00:53:43,530 --> 00:53:45,660
And I lived in Korea
until I was seven.

883
00:53:45,930 --> 00:53:47,660
Then my family and I moved
to the US.

884
00:53:50,430 --> 00:53:52,970
The Sister who looked after my mom
and me...

885
00:53:53,300 --> 00:53:58,170
apparently kept getting updates
from my adoptive parents about me.

886
00:53:58,940 --> 00:54:01,780
Why? To give them to your birth mom?

887
00:54:02,740 --> 00:54:04,510
I'm not sure about that.

888
00:54:05,880 --> 00:54:09,550
So I'm going to ask her...

889
00:54:09,750 --> 00:54:11,720
if she's still in contact
with my birth mother.

890
00:54:12,890 --> 00:54:16,790
And? If you get in touch,
will you meet your birth mom?

891
00:54:18,790 --> 00:54:19,790
Yes.

892
00:54:20,530 --> 00:54:22,700
I've thought about it
for a really long time,

893
00:54:23,570 --> 00:54:25,430
and I'd like to meet her
at least once.

894
00:54:29,140 --> 00:54:30,140
Veronica?

895
00:54:32,840 --> 00:54:34,510
Just wait a minute, okay?

896
00:54:38,210 --> 00:54:39,210
Veronica.

897
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:42,420
I'd recognize you anywhere
from your pictures.

898
00:54:42,980 --> 00:54:44,150
Hello, Sister.

899
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:49,560
So I guess she didn't come
to our house on purpose.

900
00:54:51,660 --> 00:54:54,030
(3H Acupressure Bed)

901
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:57,530
- Welcome.
- Hello.

902
00:54:57,600 --> 00:55:00,300
- You're early. Please, have a seat.
- Okay.

903
00:55:02,870 --> 00:55:06,410
These are the documents I prepared
on store management.

904
00:55:06,680 --> 00:55:07,680
Okay.

905
00:55:08,140 --> 00:55:11,080
So, for the customers
with a purchase history...

906
00:55:11,380 --> 00:55:12,950
Their information is all
in the system, right?

907
00:55:13,380 --> 00:55:14,480
Of course.

908
00:55:14,850 --> 00:55:17,450
I'll show you how to place orders
and do the closing procedures.

909
00:55:17,950 --> 00:55:18,950
Okay.

910
00:55:24,930 --> 00:55:26,830
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

911
00:55:38,740 --> 00:55:41,910
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

912
00:55:53,190 --> 00:55:56,560
Hello, Sister. What's this about?

913
00:55:58,760 --> 00:56:01,030
Yes, I can talk for a bit now.

914
00:56:17,650 --> 00:56:18,680
What's wrong?

915
00:56:19,280 --> 00:56:20,280
Why are you crying?

916
00:56:21,480 --> 00:56:22,480
Eun Bin...

917
00:56:22,780 --> 00:56:24,550
Why? What happened?

918
00:56:26,220 --> 00:56:27,320
My mom...

919
00:56:29,120 --> 00:56:30,830
My birth mom...

920
00:56:31,430 --> 00:56:34,230
Go on. What did she say?

921
00:56:36,630 --> 00:56:38,630
She doesn't want to meet me.

922
00:56:41,640 --> 00:56:44,370
Her family now is
too important to her,

923
00:56:46,940 --> 00:56:48,980
so she can't meet me.

924
00:57:02,760 --> 00:57:05,390
Okay, one, two.

925
00:57:05,930 --> 00:57:09,100
One, two. You're doing great.

926
00:57:09,330 --> 00:57:12,570
- You did great. Now, I'll show you.
- Okay.

927
00:57:12,630 --> 00:57:14,270
All right, past your ankle bone,

928
00:57:14,340 --> 00:57:18,370
just walk slowly,
like you're pedaling a bike.

929
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:21,040
- Okay, slowly.
- I think she's feeling good today.

930
00:57:21,040 --> 00:57:22,210
Okay, model, you're up.

931
00:57:22,680 --> 00:57:25,710
Are we sure we should
just drop this bomb?

932
00:57:28,350 --> 00:57:31,150
I'll handle it. Don't worry.

933
00:57:31,450 --> 00:57:33,350
Thank you for all your hard work.

934
00:57:33,860 --> 00:57:37,390
- Great work today.
- You too.

935
00:57:37,530 --> 00:57:38,930
- We're counting on you.
- Of course.

936
00:57:38,990 --> 00:57:40,230
- Yes.
- I just hope I do a good job.

937
00:57:40,300 --> 00:57:42,230
- See you next time.
- Okay.

938
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:48,200
Director Yang, didn't you say
you wanted to talk to me?

939
00:57:49,470 --> 00:57:50,710
Yes. Shall we go somewhere?

940
00:58:03,990 --> 00:58:07,220
Why? What did you want to say
that required a heads-up?

941
00:58:09,990 --> 00:58:11,030
Well...

942
00:58:11,960 --> 00:58:14,430
Actually, I was about to ask
to see you anyway.

943
00:58:16,030 --> 00:58:17,030
You were?

944
00:58:17,500 --> 00:58:19,230
There's something...

945
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:21,700
I really need to talk to you about.

946
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:24,870
In that case, please go ahead.

947
00:58:30,310 --> 00:58:32,110
I'm so sorry about this.

948
00:58:32,850 --> 00:58:35,750
I'm afraid we'll have to
revise the contract...

949
00:58:35,950 --> 00:58:38,150
or maybe even terminate it.

950
00:58:41,920 --> 00:58:44,290
I have stage two breast cancer.

951
00:58:46,290 --> 00:58:48,830
- What?
- I have to have surgery soon,

952
00:58:49,200 --> 00:58:52,530
so I think I'll have to quit
right after the fashion show.

953
00:58:54,140 --> 00:58:55,370
Wait, I mean...

954
00:58:56,170 --> 00:58:59,470
So, does that mean
if you have the surgery...

955
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:01,640
Then you'll be okay?

956
00:59:03,750 --> 00:59:05,350
We'll have to see how it goes.

957
00:59:08,820 --> 00:59:10,020
Are you okay?

958
00:59:12,150 --> 00:59:13,150
No.

959
00:59:16,820 --> 00:59:20,030
So that's why you've seemed
so exhausted.

960
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:21,530
And I had no idea.

961
00:59:22,800 --> 00:59:24,830
I feel so terrible.

962
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:29,540
That actually makes me feel
a bit better.

963
00:59:30,140 --> 00:59:32,640
That's a better reaction
than I got from my own husband.

964
00:59:33,570 --> 00:59:35,310
You're going to make me cry.

965
00:59:35,980 --> 00:59:37,310
Dr. Han...

966
00:59:38,910 --> 00:59:40,050
I have a favor to ask.

967
00:59:41,780 --> 00:59:43,180
Please...

968
00:59:43,820 --> 00:59:45,450
keep this a secret from Ju Ah.

969
00:59:46,350 --> 00:59:48,490
This is something
she's wanted so badly.

970
00:59:49,220 --> 00:59:50,930
The last thing she needs now
is her mom...

971
00:59:51,260 --> 00:59:53,460
getting in her way,
especially since she was against it.

972
00:59:54,960 --> 00:59:56,630
I want to see this through.

973
00:59:58,700 --> 01:00:01,840
Please. Don't tell her.

974
01:00:06,940 --> 01:00:08,280
The lighting...

975
01:00:11,780 --> 01:00:13,210
Just a little...

976
01:00:23,690 --> 01:00:24,890
And then...

977
01:00:25,460 --> 01:00:27,230
The second chandelier.

978
01:00:32,830 --> 01:00:34,970
We turn this off as she walks.

979
01:00:35,970 --> 01:00:37,040
Next...

980
01:00:40,110 --> 01:00:41,710
Did you tell her?
Did you get in trouble?

981
01:00:42,940 --> 01:00:43,950
No.

982
01:00:44,080 --> 01:00:45,410
What do you mean, no?

983
01:00:45,410 --> 01:00:47,350
Did you not tell her?
Or she didn't yell at you?

984
01:00:48,720 --> 01:00:49,750
Both.

985
01:00:51,850 --> 01:00:53,350
You couldn't tell her, could you?

986
01:00:59,230 --> 01:01:03,970
Yes, I'm sure it was tough.
Mom did seem a little on edge today.

987
01:01:04,630 --> 01:01:06,070
We'll find another time.

988
01:01:11,570 --> 01:01:12,770
Want a hug?

989
01:01:13,840 --> 01:01:14,910
Are you crazy?

990
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:23,820
I'll make you a promise.

991
01:01:25,190 --> 01:01:28,090
- What is it?
- No matter what anyone says to you,

992
01:01:28,520 --> 01:01:30,290
I am never going to leave you.

993
01:01:31,030 --> 01:01:32,290
You'd better not.

994
01:01:33,760 --> 01:01:34,830
So...

995
01:01:37,730 --> 01:01:40,940
No matter what happens,
you can talk to me.

996
01:01:41,000 --> 01:01:43,770
You can lean on me
and depend on me, okay?

997
01:01:44,340 --> 01:01:45,410
Of course.

998
01:01:45,840 --> 01:01:49,940
I'll make sure
you never get hurt or upset.

999
01:01:50,710 --> 01:01:51,910
I'll protect you.

1000
01:01:54,420 --> 01:01:55,420
You trust me, right?

1001
01:01:55,720 --> 01:01:57,120
Yes, I do.

1002
01:02:00,290 --> 01:02:02,790
What's gotten into you?
Why are you being so sweet today?

1003
01:02:05,230 --> 01:02:07,200
So, what did Director Yang say?

1004
01:02:07,830 --> 01:02:09,660
He said there's no need
to terminate the contract.

1005
01:02:10,030 --> 01:02:12,970
But if I quit working,
my public profile will drop,

1006
01:02:13,270 --> 01:02:16,740
and I lose my value as a model,
so I shouldn't get my hopes up.

1007
01:02:17,440 --> 01:02:21,040
That's it? Did he say anything else?

1008
01:02:21,640 --> 01:02:25,550
No. I asked him not to tell Ju Ah
or his family,

1009
01:02:26,050 --> 01:02:28,080
but I'm not sure
if he'll keep his promise.

1010
01:02:29,720 --> 01:02:32,120
He will. He's very tight-lipped.

1011
01:02:32,890 --> 01:02:35,620
Exactly. He's so much better
than Gong Jeong Han.

1012
01:02:36,660 --> 01:02:41,030
He felt so terrible for me.
His eyes were welling up with tears.

1013
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:43,430
He almost made me cry too.

1014
01:02:44,670 --> 01:02:47,400
Anyway, your son is
really something else.

1015
01:02:47,940 --> 01:02:50,770
The way he acted,
you'd think I just have the flu.

1016
01:02:51,470 --> 01:02:55,380
Any other husband would care more,
even over the flu.

1017
01:02:55,980 --> 01:02:58,510
I know.
I was disappointed in him too.

1018
01:03:00,210 --> 01:03:03,680
Still, it's better than him crying
and making a scene.

1019
01:03:07,020 --> 01:03:08,320
Jeong Han, are you almost done?
Let's go.

1020
01:03:09,790 --> 01:03:10,860
What the... Where did he go?

1021
01:03:12,390 --> 01:03:13,390
Jeong Han.

1022
01:03:19,570 --> 01:03:20,570
Jeong Han?

1023
01:03:22,940 --> 01:03:24,010
Hey, why are you crying?

1024
01:03:24,840 --> 01:03:27,440
What? It's nothing.

1025
01:03:29,980 --> 01:03:30,980
What's wrong?

1026
01:03:31,880 --> 01:03:33,110
Why? What's wrong?

1027
01:03:35,880 --> 01:03:36,880
Dae Han.

1028
01:03:38,320 --> 01:03:40,020
What am I going to do?

1029
01:03:40,760 --> 01:03:44,030
What do you mean?
Why? What's the matter?

1030
01:03:46,130 --> 01:03:47,260
It's Seong Mi.

1031
01:03:48,760 --> 01:03:50,160
She has breast cancer.

1032
01:03:54,800 --> 01:03:55,800
What?

1033
01:03:56,270 --> 01:03:59,370
I'm so scared.

1034
01:04:01,680 --> 01:04:02,880
Seong Mi? How?

1035
01:04:05,150 --> 01:04:06,680
I...

1036
01:04:07,550 --> 01:04:09,520
I gave her such a hard time...

1037
01:04:10,020 --> 01:04:12,690
I can't help thinking it's my fault.
I just...

1038
01:04:13,190 --> 01:04:17,230
I can't even look her in the eye.
Gosh, I'm losing my mind.

1039
01:04:22,030 --> 01:04:23,330
Man...

1040
01:04:27,170 --> 01:04:31,070
Hey, what if something happens
to my Seong Mi?

1041
01:04:31,140 --> 01:04:32,940
What will I do? My Seong Mi...
What should I do?

1042
01:04:35,710 --> 01:04:36,980
My Seong Mi.

1043
01:04:37,310 --> 01:04:41,380
No. Nothing can happen
to my Seong Mi.

1044
01:05:06,940 --> 01:05:09,680
(Recipe For Love)

1045
01:05:10,510 --> 01:05:13,950
What if Mom is so shocked
she messes up the fashion show?

1046
01:05:14,520 --> 01:05:16,420
What if your brother finds out?

1047
01:05:16,480 --> 01:05:19,390
He's at lunch, so he won't find out.
Gosh, you scared me!

1048
01:05:19,720 --> 01:05:23,090
If someone's out of contact for long
and we can't confirm they're okay,

1049
01:05:23,160 --> 01:05:24,790
that's grounds for filing
a missing person report.

1050
01:05:25,260 --> 01:05:27,800
- What? A tailor shop? Right here!
- A tailor shop!

1051
01:05:28,400 --> 01:05:29,730
Did you two have a fight?

1052
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:33,330
- You two acted like sisters.
- Sisters?

1053
01:05:36,000 --> 01:05:37,170
What are you looking for?
